a major loss to their honor, piecing their lives back together often results in children being raised by single mothers without support from the fathers. Maria has 2 children, ages 5 and 7. She says they are good students and above average in their studies.

"My husband and I met at a drinking party. He promised to love and take care of me. After marriage, I worked and looked after our children at home. He stayed out late and chased women. When I asked him to stop, he sometimes beat me.

"I was disappointed by my husband. He never provided any money for the family. One day, he came home drunk and beat me. I didn't let him get away with hitting me. I grabbed him and beat him in return. In rage, he slapped me on the face and I bit his finger.

"Realizing that he wasn't the man I knew, I left and stayed with my mom until I had enough money to start a business with Cong Banh. At the time, we gave tailoring jobs to other people and paid them by the project.
